Aim
To perform host discovery in a network using Nmap ping scan and identify active hosts in the subnet range.
Introduction
Nmap (Network Mapper) is an open-source network scanning tool used for network discovery and security
auditing. It helps identify active hosts, open ports, running services, and vulnerabilities in a network.
A ping scan is used to discover live systems without performing detailed port scanning. It helps network
administrators and cybersecurity professionals monitor devices connected to the network.
Procedure
Step 1: Install Nmap
Open Kali Linux terminal and install Nmap using:
sudo apt install nmap -y
Step 2: Verify Installation
Check whether Nmap is installed successfully:
nmap --version
Step 3: Identify Network Range
Check the local IP address:
ip addr
Step 4: Perform Host Discovery
Run the Nmap ping scan command:
nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24
Step 5: Analyze Output
Observe the active hosts displayed in the scan result.
Implementation
Command Used
nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24
Explanation
• nmap → Starts Nmap tool
• -sn → Ping scan only
• 192.168.1.0/24 → Target subnet range
Output
Nmap scan report for 192.168.1.1
Host is up
Nmap scan report for 192.168.1.5
Host is up
Result
Thus, host discovery using Nmap ping scan was performed successfully and active hosts in the network were
identified.
